Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
lminus(25.10)                                                    lminus(25.10)

Name
       lminus  -  Subtracts  the specified elements in the second list (list2)
       from the first specified list (list1)

Syntax
       lminus

       [-exact]

       <list1>

       <list2>

       Subtracts the specified elements in the second list  (list2)  from  the
       first specified list (list1) .

Parameters
       -exact Searches for an exact match.

       <list1>
              Specifies the list from which elements must be removed.

       <list2>
              Specifies the list of elements to be subtracted.

Examples
              * The following command subtracts the elements from list l2 from
                list l1.

                innovus> set l1 {a a* ab2 b1 b2 c}

                innovus> set l2 {a c}

                innovus> lminus $l1 $l2

                a* ab2 b1 b2

              * The  following command subtracts a list consisting of a* and c
                from the list of elements of l1.

                innovus> lminus $l1 {a* c}

                b1 b2

              * The following command uses an exact search.

                innovus> lminus -exact $l1 {a* c}

                a ab2 b1 b2

